  "prompt": "Which is the best camera phone performance under 10000?",
  "response": "As of October 2023, there are several smartphones under \u20b910,000 in the Indian market that offer impressive camera performance. Here's a breakdown of some of the top contenders:\n\n### 1. **POCO M4 Pro**\n- **Camera Setup:**\n  - **Main Camera:** 64MP, f/1.89, (wide), PDAF\n  - **Additional Cameras:** 2MP macro, 2MP depth sensor\n- **Key Features:**\n  - **Display:** 6.43-inch FHD+ AMOLED, 90Hz refresh rate\n  - **Processor:** MediaTek Dimensity 810\n  - **Battery:** 5000mAh with 33W fast charging\n- **Why It Stands Out:**\n  - The 64MP main sensor captures detailed and vibrant images.\n  - AMOLED display ensures accurate color reproduction, enhancing photo previews.\n  - Balanced performance with a capable processor for smooth operation.\n\n### 2. **Redmi Note 11**\n- **Camera Setup:**\n  - **Main Camera:** 50MP, f/1.8, (wide), PDAF\n  - **Additional Cameras:** 8MP ultra-wide, 2MP macro, 2MP depth sensor\n- **Key Features:**\n  - **Display:** 6.43-inch FHD+ AMOLED, 90Hz refresh rate\n  - **Processor:** Qualcomm Snapdragon 680\n  - **Battery:** 5000mAh with 33W fast charging\n- **Why It Stands Out:**\n  - Reliable 50MP main camera with good color accuracy and detail.\n  - Versatile camera setup suitable for various photography styles.\n  - Clean MIUI experience with regular updates.\n\n### 3. **realme Narzo 50A**\n- **Camera Setup:**\n  - **Main Camera:** 50MP, f/1.8, (wide)\n  - **Additional Cameras:** 2MP macro, 2MP depth sensor\n- **Key Features:**\n  - **Display:** 6.5-inch HD+ IPS LCD, 90Hz refresh rate\n  - **Processor:** MediaTek Helio G85\n  - **Battery:** 6000mAh with 18W fast charging\n- **Why It Stands Out:**\n  - Large 50MP sensor provides good image quality in well-lit conditions.\n  - Massive 6000mAh battery ensures long usage between charges.\n  - Affordable pricing with decent overall performance.\n\n### 4. **Samsung Galaxy M32**\n- **Camera Setup:**\n  - **Main Camera:** 64MP, f/1.8, (wide), PDAF\n  - **Additional Cameras:** 8MP ultra-wide, 2MP macro, 2MP depth sensor\n- **Key Features:**\n  - **Display:** 6.4-inch FHD+ Super AMOLED, 90Hz refresh rate\n  - **Processor:** MediaTek Helio G80\n  - **Battery:** 6000mAh with 25W fast charging\n- **Why It Stands Out:**\n  - Samsung's renowned image processing delivers natural and balanced photos.\n  - Super AMOLED display offers vibrant visuals for photo viewing.\n  - Sturdy build quality with a sleek design.\n\n### 5. **Motorola Moto G31**\n- **Camera Setup:**\n  - **Main Camera:** 50MP, f/1.8, (wide), PDAF\n  - **Additional Cameras:** 8MP ultra-wide, 2MP depth sensor\n- **Key Features:**\n  - **Display:** 6.4-inch OLED, 90Hz refresh rate\n  - **Processor:** MediaTek Helio G85\n  - **Battery:** 5000mAh with 30W fast charging\n- **Why It Stands Out:**\n  - Clean Android experience with minimal bloatware.\n  - Good camera performance with accurate colors.\n  - Attractive OLED display in this price segment.\n\n### **Conclusion**\n\nWhile all the above smartphones offer commendable camera performance within the \u20b910,000 budget, the **POCO M4 Pro** often stands out due to its higher-resolution main camera and balanced overall features. However, your choice might vary based on specific preferences such as brand loyalty, display quality, battery life, or software experience. It's advisable to check the latest prices and user reviews, as prices can fluctuate and new models might have been released since the last update.",
